  <refnamediv>
    <refname>&amp;</refname>

    <refpurpose>logical and operator</refpurpose>
  </refnamediv>

  <refsynopsisdiv>
    <title>Calling Sequence</title>

    <synopsis>A&amp;B</synopsis>
  </refsynopsisdiv>

  <refsection>
    <title>Description</title>

    <para><literal>A&amp;B</literal> gives the element-wise logical
    <literal>and</literal> of the booleans matrices
    <literal>A</literal> and <literal>B</literal>. Matrices
    <literal>A</literal> and <literal>B</literal> must have the same
    dimensions or one from them must be a single boolean.</para>

    <para> Used inside an if or while condition expression the &amp;
    operator short circuits (do not evaluates) the second operand
    evaluation if the first one evaluates to false.</para>
   <para>If one of the operand evaluates to an empty matrix <literal>[ ]</literal> the following rules apply:</para>
    <para>[]&amp;[] == []</para>
    <para>[]&amp;A == A</para>   
    <para>A&amp;[] == A</para>   
 

  </refsection>

